<1ST_LINE>u a AM-ChemicalFumes     06-22 0181</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Chemical Fumes,0185</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Employees Spray Lysol on Ant Repellant, Create Noxious Fumes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HUDSON, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A disinfectant used to temper a strong odor
of spilled ant repellant unleashed noxious fumes that forced the
evacuation Tuesday of a shopping center, authorities said.
   At least 50 employees and customers of the Jamesway department
store in Greenport were treated and released at Columbia-Greene
Medical Center and one person was admitted, said Deputy Reggie
Crowley of the Columbia County Sheriff's Department.
   Most of the people were treated for minor breathing problems and
eye irritation, said Anne Grebert, a hospital spokeswoman. One
person was held overnight for observation, she said.
   After an 8-ounce bottle of ant repellant was spilled in the
store, employees sprayed about a half-dozen cans of Lysol
disinfectant to mask the strong odor, Crowley said.
   The mixture produced fumes that forced the evacuation of the
store and later the Jamesway shopping plaza, including about 12
other stores, Crowley said.
   He said that a hazardous waste cleanup team would inspect the
site, about 30 miles south of Albany, before the stores reopened.
</TEXT>
