<TEXT>
   Singer Mel Torme says it doesn't
bother him in the least that his new popularity is due in part to
the NBC comedy ``Night Court.''
   ``It is ironic that the younger people have learned about me
that way, but I'm grateful for it,'' said Torme, who is depicted as
the musical hero of the show's main character, Judge Harold T.
Stone, played by Harry Anderson.
   ``Any way you can be remembered, if it works, then it's
terrific. I'm delighted for what ``Night Court'' has done for me,''
he said recently.
   The 62-year-old entertainer, who has been performing since he
was 4, is preparing to release his autobiography, ``It Wasn't All
Velvet,'' and is working on a biography of the late jazz drummer
Buddy Rich.
