<HEAD>Fireman Injured, Arrests In Protest Against Eviction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BASEL, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fireman was seriously burned by a
Molotov cocktail and 23 protesters were arrested during a night of
riots after police shut down an alternative culture center,
authorities said today.
   Basel police used tear gas and rubber bullets Tuesday night to
disperse about 1,000 demonstrators, some of whom threw stones and
Molotov cocktails, smashed windows of city buildings and set
garbage on fire.
   A city square near the culture center ressembled the remnants of
``a bomb attack,'' police chief Robert Heuss said.
   One fireman who was hit by a Molotov cocktail suffered
third-degree burns on his face and hands, police said. No injuries
were reported among the protesters.
   The violence came after police evicted about 60 squatters before
dawn Tuesday from an old city greenhouse complex housing the
center. The occupants had defied an official ultimatum to vacate
the site, which Basel residents decided in a May referendum to turn
into a park.
