<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Ancient Massacre,0134</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mass Killing Took Place More Than Millennium Ago</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LYON, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The people of Landaize, one of whom recently
dug up five skeletons under his house, were relieved to learn that
their village was not the scene of a massacre _ at least not
recently.
   Santos Martin, a resident of Landaize, near Lyon, came upon the
skeletons of two men, one woman and two children while digging in
his basement, officials said Tuesday.
   Experts who examined the skeletons said the bones dated from the
sixth century A.D., when Germanic tribes battled to take over this
region of Burgundy.
   The expert opinion was important for the villagers, said Robert
Vilain of the National Center for Scientific Research. They had
already begun throwing suspicious glances at their neighbors.
</TEXT>
