<HEAD>Baryshnikov to Have Surgery, Cancels Nationwide Tour</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates throughout with entire tour canceled</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mikhail Baryshnikov will undergo knee surgery
next week and has canceled a nationwide tour, spokesmen said
Wednesday.
   Baryshnikov, artistic director of the American Ballet Theater,
had scheduled 28 dance performances of his own, from Arlington,
Texas, on July 1 to Columbus, Ohio, on Aug. 7, said spokesman
Bernie Lawrence.
   The surgery, to correct ``an aggravated condition of his knee,''
will be performed at an undisclosed New York City hospital,
possibly Tuesday, by William Hamilton, Lawrence said.
   A secretary at Hamilton's office referred calls to the ABT.
   ``The subsequent recovery period will be determined by the
findings at surgery,'' said a statement issued by Baryshnikov's
publicist, Edgar Vincent.
   Baryshnikov also has canceled several festival appearances in
Europe, although Lawrence could not immediately say where they were.
