<1ST_LINE>r i AM-SAfrica-Blast     06-22 0184</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-SAfrica-Blast,0190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Limpet Mine at Game Arcade Injures 10</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A limpet mine exploded at a
game arcade in downtown Johannesburg on Wednesday, injuring 10
people, including a pregnant woman and her 2-year-old daughter,
police said.
   The facade of the arcade, featuring video games and pinball
machines, was blown out by the explosion and a fire flared briefly
before being extinguished.
   Police Col. Frans Malherbe said the injured included six blacks,
one white and three people of Indian descent, including the
pregnant woman, her husband and their daughter.
   Malherbe said four of the victims were seriously hurt.
   The arcade, Winning Games Center, is on the ground floor of an
apartment building. Residents were ordered to evacuate as police
searched for evidence.
   There have been more than 20 bombings and hand grenade attacks
in South Africa this year, killing eight people and injuring 59.
   The government has blamed the attacks on the outlawed African
National Congress guerrilla movement. The ANC has not claimed
responsibility for specific attacks in recent months but has said
it seeks to intensify its guerrilla operations.
</TEXT>
