<HEAD>Gold Shipment Vanishes On Way to New York</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 55-pound shipment of gold bullion
disappeared en route from New York to Belgrade earlier this month,
the daily Politika Ekspres reported Wednesday.
   The newspaper said the shipment, worth $363,000, has been
missing since June 10 when it was due to have arrived at Belgrade
airport on a regular Yugoslav Airlines flight.
   A police investigation has turned up no trace of the gold, which
was destined for a major Yugoslav jewelry manufacturer, the
newspaper said. It said police speculate the bullion may have been
accidentally shipped to another destination.
</TEXT>
