<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--AldridgeTrip     06-22 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Aldridge Trip,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Air Force Secretary To Visit Soviet Union</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Air Force Secretary Edward C. Aldridge will
visit space and military facilities in the Soviet Union early next
month at the invitation of Russia's defense minister, the Pentagon
said Wednesday.
   The visit, scheduled July 3-8, will include ``visits to a
space-launch facility in central Asia and the cosmonaut training
center at Star City and Soviet military installations,'' the
Pentagon said.
   ``During his stay, Secretary Aldridge will also meet with
representatives of the Soviet defense, air force and space
communities to discuss developments and capabilities of the Soviet
space program.''
   The Pentagon said Aldridge had been invited to make the trip by
Soviet Defense Minister Dmitri Yazov. His host while in Russia will
be Marshall of Aviation Aleksandr N. Yefimov, the deputy minister
of defense and commander-in-chief of the Soviet air forces, the
Pentagon said.
</TEXT>
