<HEAD>Landslide Kills 14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A landslide in southern China has killed 14
people and seven others are missing, a newspaper reported Thursday.
   The official People's Daily (Remnin Ribao) said the landslide in
the village of Xiayuan in southern China's Jiangxi province Tuesday
covered nearly 10 acres of land with mud and stone and destroyed 29
houses.
   Thirty-seven people were seriously injured, the report said.
   The report did not say what caused the landslide.
</TEXT>
