<HEAD>Allegheny Internation Seeks Name Change</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Allegheny International Inc. says it plans to
change its name to Sunbeam Corp. once the troubled company emerges
from reorganization under federal bankruptcy laws.
   The company disclosed its intention in a reorganization plan
filed Monday in U.S. Bankruptcy Court.
   Allegheny International said most company products carry the
Sunbeam label. The name switch also will help the company repair an
image damaged when it shed its old management and entered
bankruptcy proceedings.
