<HEAD>Mercedes Benz Forsm Sales Company With Mitsubishi Motors</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Japanese subsidiary of Daimler Benz AG of West
Germany said Wednesday it had established a joint venture with
Mitsubishi Motors Corp. of Japan to market Mercedes-Benz
automobiles in Japan.
   Kazuhiro Joh, a spokesman of Mercedes-Benz Japan Co., said the
venture, called Stuttgart Auto Service Inc., is owned 51 percent by
Mercedes-Benz Japan and 49 percent by Mitsubishi Motors.
   Joh said the new company plans to sell more than 5,000
Mercedes-Benz passengers a year in Japan through its own and
Mitsubishi Motors' sales networks. That figure could rise to 30,000
cars annually by 1992.
   Joh said 18,749 cars were sold in Japan last year mostly through
the Japanese distributor, Yanase and Co.
